The United States strongly condemns the recent terrorist attack in Mogadishu, Somalia, which resulted in the death of around 100 people and the injury of approximately 300 others. The attack targeted the Somali Ministry of Education and first responders, which makes it even more heinous. The United States expresses its deepest condolences to the Somali people and all those affected by this senseless act of violence against innocent civilians. The U.S. remains dedicated to supporting the Federal Government of Somalia in its efforts to combat such heartless terrorist acts.